26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_mmu_nv41.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "nv04.h"
30
31#include <core/gpuobj.h>
32#include <core/option.h>
33#include <subdev/timer.h>
34
35#define NV41_GART_SIZE (512 * 1024 * 1024)
36#define NV41_GART_PAGE ( 4 * 1024)
37
38/*******************************************************************************
39 * VM map/unmap callbacks
40 ******************************************************************************/
41
42static void
43nv41_vm_map_sg(struct nvkm_vma *vma, struct nvkm_memory *pgt,
44 struct nvkm_mem *mem, u32 pte, u32 cnt, dma_addr_t *list)
45{
46 pte = pte * 4;
47 nvkm_kmap(pgt);
48 while (cnt) {
49 u32 page = PAGE_SIZE / NV41_GART_PAGE;
50 u64 phys = (u64)*list++;
51 while (cnt && page--) {
52 nvkm_wo32(pgt, pte, (phys >> 7) | 1);
53 phys += NV41_GART_PAGE;
54 pte += 4;
55 cnt -= 1;
56 }
57 }
58 nvkm_done(pgt);
59}
60
61static void
62nv41_vm_unmap(struct nvkm_vma *vma, struct nvkm_memory *pgt, u32 pte, u32 cnt)
63{
64 pte = pte * 4;
65 nvkm_kmap(pgt);
66 while (cnt--) {
67 nvkm_wo32(pgt, pte, 0x00000000);
68 pte += 4;
69 }
70 nvkm_done(pgt);
71}
72
73static void
74nv41_vm_flush(struct nvkm_vm *vm)
75{
76 struct nv04_mmu *mmu = nv04_mmu(vm->mmu);
77 struct nvkm_device *device = mmu->base.subdev.device;
78
79 mutex_lock(&mmu->base.subdev.mutex);
80 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100810, 0x00000022);
81 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
82 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100810) & 0x00000020)
83 break;
84 );
85 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100810, 0x00000000);
86 mutex_unlock(&mmu->base.subdev.mutex);
87}
88
89/*******************************************************************************
90 * MMU subdev
91 ******************************************************************************/
92
93static int
94nv41_mmu_oneinit(struct nvkm_mmu *base)
95{
96 struct nv04_mmu *mmu = nv04_mmu(base);
97 struct nvkm_device *device = mmu->base.subdev.device;
98 int ret;
99
100 ret = nvkm_vm_create(&mmu->base, 0, NV41_GART_SIZE, 0, 4096, NULL,
101 &mmu->vm);
102 if (ret)
103 return ret;
104
105 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST,
106 (NV41_GART_SIZE / NV41_GART_PAGE) * 4, 16, true,
107 &mmu->vm->pgt[0].mem[0]);
108 mmu->vm->pgt[0].refcount[0] = 1;
109 return ret;
110}
111
112static void
113nv41_mmu_init(struct nvkm_mmu *base)
114{
115 struct nv04_mmu *mmu = nv04_mmu(base);
116 struct nvkm_device *device = mmu->base.subdev.device;
117 struct nvkm_memory *dma = mmu->vm->pgt[0].mem[0];
118 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100800, 0x00000002 | nvkm_memory_addr(dma));
119 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10008c, 0x00000100, 0x00000100);
120 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100820, 0x00000000);
121}
122
123static const struct nvkm_mmu_func
124nv41_mmu = {
125 .dtor = nv04_mmu_dtor,
126 .oneinit = nv41_mmu_oneinit,
127 .init = nv41_mmu_init,
128 .limit = NV41_GART_SIZE,
129 .dma_bits = 39,
130 .pgt_bits = 32 - 12,
131 .spg_shift = 12,
132 .lpg_shift = 12,
133 .map_sg = nv41_vm_map_sg,
134 .unmap = nv41_vm_unmap,
135 .flush = nv41_vm_flush,
136};
137
138int
139nv41_mmu_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_mmu **pmmu)
140{
141 if (device->type == NVKM_DEVICE_AGP ||
142 !nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, "NvPCIE", true))
143 return nv04_mmu_new(device, index, pmmu);
144
145 return nv04_mmu_new_(&nv41_mmu, device, index, pmmu);
146}
